recordings.loc: Alachua, Alachua County, Florida
recordings.rmk:
It was singing from a live-oak tree in my front yard but despite my attempts I did not see the bird.  It has been singing from that tree for a week or so.  This clip is repeated every 20-30 seconds and does not vary.  I haven't heard any other song that I would attribute to this same bird.

High pass filter to remove traffic noise and clipped to just this bird, otherwise un-modified. Typical US sub-urban environment, in fact this was recorded on my front porch. Mix of sub-urban yards.

recordings.loc: Westport, Bristol, Massachusetts
recordings.file-name: XC144030-Gooseberry Island - Westport - MA - USA - Setophaga magnolia (Magnolia Warbler) flight call - 7-30-2013 - Paul Champlin.mp3
recordings.rmk: This is a hatch-year bird seen at Gooseberry Island, Westport, Massachusetts - a migrant funnel point. The bird was seen leaving a bush and migrating to the mainland with several Yellow Warblers. At first, a flight photo taken consecutive to the perched bird proved to be S. magnolia, but the recording is of the perched bird as it took flight, and photos of the perched bird proved to be S. discolor.
